radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is mildly hyperemic and fluid-filled and slightly enlarged in caliber measuring up to 1 cm. Minimal fat stranding is noted. No drainable collection. No extraluminal air. Visualized lung fields are within normal limits. No evidence of pleural or pericardial effusion. The liver, pancreas, spleen, adrenal glands, kidneys, stomach, small bowel, colon, rectum, urinary bladder, and distal ureters are all within normal limits.
